				<pubDate>Wed, 07 Jun 2017 21:28:20 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Kid F</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2782678</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>SCP-3850 is a phenomenon centered around a body</p> </blockquote> <p>It's a really tiny nitpick, but one that bugs me nonetheless: how can something be centered <em>around</em> something else? Logically, if it's centered on something, then that something should be a specific, single point (i.e. &quot;centered <em>on</em> a body&quot;). Might just be a dumb concern, so I won't edit.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
