					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2280344#post-2831414</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2280344/scp-3850#post-2831414</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 24 May 2017 19:05:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>altpera</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3081811</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The more I read it, the more I love this article. The imagery is among the most disturbing I've come across on the site:</p> <blockquote> <p>The skydiver's body is currently visible and suspended above SCP-3850-1</p> </blockquote> <p>It's so haunting, and the clinical tone of the SCP makes it even more strange. I really, really like that. A great example of less is more; personally, I don't think it needs in depth containment procedures or further exploration logs. It works because the imagery itself is so disturbing. A new favourite!<br /> +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
